<item>
            <title>[LU-3320] Single 2.6-rhel6.series for lustre kernel patches whereas ldiskfs kernel patches support multiple 2.6-rhel&apos;s</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3320</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There recent RHEL 6.4 kernel update from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2846&quot; title=&quot;Kernel update [RHEL6.4 2.6.32-358.2.1.el6]&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2846&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2846&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; broke builds on RHEL 6.3.  That&apos;s because there is only one series file for 2.6-rhel6 and one of the new patches shouldn&apos;t be applied to RHEL 6.3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ldiskfs kernel patches have two series files, ldiskfs-2.6-rhel6.series and ldiskfs-2.6-rhel6.4.series.  If that solution would be acceptable for the ldiskfs patch sets, then hopefully the same approach ought to be acceptable for the lustre kernel patches. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
